Many other schools have April 15 deadlines, so I just wanted to check if we might even hear back from Berkeley before then. Any/all input is greatly appreciated!

From Michael when I asked him when the official grad admission decision will come out:

Probably the second week of April, as we wrap up regular deadline application reviews/ decisions. The April 15th SIR deadline is a soft deadline, so you are able to SIR even far beyond that date.

history.content:
We're still reviewing 5th Yr MS applications. The SIR deadline is a soft deadline and we're hopeful to have departmental emails sent out within the next couple of days. Usually it takes GradDiv 24-48 hours to vet the department recommendations and then they'll follow up with official offer letters. I will address this in the departmental emails, but if you're admitted then we'd like you to SIR by the end of April at the latest.

Thanks,

Michael

p.s. regarding MEng decisions -- if you emailed us you would have received this canned reply about it--

"At this time, most EECS offers of admission have already been communicated to those applicants.  Thank you for your patience in this process, as the EECS MEng received over 2,000 applications with an admissions rate of around 12%.

We hope to have all final decisions communicated no later than the end of April. MEng applicants will receive only one final decision from Berkeley: an offer of admission or denial from the EECS department, or an offer of admission from your second choice department."

We're still reviewing 5th Yr MS applications. The SIR deadline is a soft deadline and we're hopeful to have departmental emails sent out within the next couple of days. Usually it takes GradDiv 24-48 hours to vet the department recommendations and then they'll follow up with official offer letters. I will address this in the departmental emails, but if you're admitted then we'd like you to SIR by the end of April at the latest.

Thanks,

Michael
